{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_noone_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280600714/1930042801/0667.xml":{"full_text":"A-6\nHONESTY IS URGED\nIN ADVERTISING\nt.' _______\nPublicity Chairman Outlines\nDuty Devolving Upon Asso\nciated Clubs at May Meeting.\nTo the gigantic program of business\nrevival must be added the stimulus of\nhonest advertising, Frederic W. Hume,\ngeneral chairman of the publicity com\nmittee ot the Associated Advertising\nClubs of the World, today declared in\na statement calling attention of adver\ntising men to the work to be accom\nplished at their twenty-sixth annual\nconvention here May 18 to 22.\nThe statement says:\n\"There is an unlqticf significance to\nthis event In the fact that we are fill\ning out a part of the program laid down\nby the President in his appeal for co\noperation by business men and business\norganizations to study and report basic\nconditions of business and devise rrfeth\nods of speeding up our industrial ma\nchine in order to offset certain economic\nreadjustments that took place late in\n1829. v\n\"During the past several months\ngroups of business men have been care\nfully studying existing conditions in\ntheir respective lines. The Department\nof Commerce, United States Chamber\nof Commerce, civic associations, as well\nas State and Federal boards, have con\ntributed to this research of business.\n\"In co-operation with the findings of\nthose committees of business men we\nmust lead the way in electrifying into\naction their findings. After all, adver\ntising is -what might be termed \u2018the\nelectrictty of business.\u2019\n\"We are confronted with the real\nopportunity of submitting our conclu\naive prbof of the value of advertising,\nright in the citadel of our own Gov\nernment, meeting with a common pur\npose to add that impetus through ad\nvertising that appears most vital to this\ngigantic program of business revival.\u201d\nPLANES READY TO HOP\nWITH CARGO OF FURS\nSalta From Ice-Bound Nanuk Will I\nBe Flown to Teller,\nAlaska.\nBr the Associated Press.\nMOTOR SHIP NANUK, North Cape,\nSiberia, April 28. \u2014Carrying a valuable\ncargo of furs destined for the United\n6tates and held on this Ice-bound ship\nhere aince November, two airplanes,\npiloted by Joe Crosson and S. C. Rob\nbins, were ready to leave here today on\n600-mile flight over the Arctic coast\nto Teller, Alaska.\nCrosson and Robbins arrived yester\nday from Alaska after an overnight stop\nat the Isolated lagoon to the east of\nhere, where they picked up one of the\nplanes.\nPilot Gladyshev, Russian aviator,\nyesterday left the Soviet ship Stavro\npol, Ice bound 2 miles from here, with\nthe last two members of the Moscow\nscientific expedition of more than 20\nmembers who were marooned on that\nvessel during the Winter. They were\nto fly to St. Lawrence Bay, thence to\nValdlvostok and overland to Moscow.\nKBsi\nlyjts l misSm\nReal Estate Loans\n(D. C. Property Only)\n6%\nNo Commission Charged\nYou can take 12 years to In\npay off your loan without the\nexpense of renewing. SI,OOO\nfor $lO per month, including\ninterest and principal. Larger\nor smaller loans at proportion\nate rates.\nPerpetual\nBuilding\nAssociation\nEatabliahed 1881\nLargest in Washington\nAssets Over $22,000,000\nCor. 11th and E N.W.\nJAMES BERRY. Prtildcnt\nrc^EWnA\u00dfn_C^_ji AET7. S.rrftary\nCuts\nthe\nCost\nto the\n(oast\nYou can pack tha\npleasure of tha Far\nWest Into two weeks.\nI\nYou can visit dude\nranches. National Parks,\nsnow-capped ranges and\ntake the Indian-detours.\nYou can go clear to\nCalifornia and back, on a\nSanta Fe Summer Xcursion\nticket \u2014at a faro so rea\nsonable you can afford to\ntake the whole family.\nEscorted AII-ExpenseTour*\nweekly during June* July\nand August. Every detail\ncared for by xperienced\ntravel directors.\nfor booirfeto and reservation*\naddr\u2014t\n<J. C. DILLARD\nDlst. Pass. Agent\nSANTA FE RY.\n601-602 Finance Building\nPHILADELPHIA, PA.\nB Phones: Kitten house 1464-S\n13 BOY SCOUTS GIVEN\