of\nthe National Capital, especially in re\ngard to its trees, is said to be attribu\ntable to his work. When Saunders was\nchairman of the Park Commission he\nsuperintended the planting of more\nthan 3,000 trees and participated in the\ndevelopment of the west front of the\nCapitol Park.\nThe observance here Is to be marked\nwith distinguished services for Saunders\nday, as this was his home city and\nthe birthplace of the grange. Saunders\nday also will be observed throughout\nthe country. At the local ceremonies\nA. M. Loomis of the National Grange\nwill show pictures of the results of\nSaunders\u2019 work.\nThe committee of Potomac Grange\nincludes A. M. Loomis, Mrs. Mabel R.\nCox, who is a granddaughter of Mr.\nSaunders; R. W. Dunlap, L. A. Esta\nbrook, H. E. Allanson, P. L. Plyler and\nE. C. Powell.\nMRS. INCE\u2019S WEDDING DAY\nLOS ANGELES. April 28 UP).\u2014 Plans\nfor the wedding May 15 of Mrs. Elinor\nKersaw Ince, 45, widow of Thomas\nInce, motion picture producer, and\nHolmes Herbert, 47, screen player, were\nbeing made here today.\nMrs. Ince\u2019s marriage to Herbert will\ndeprive her of her share of the $1,600,-\n000 Ince estate, as under the terms of\nher late husband's will she is to receive\nonly the interest from her share in the\nevent of her remarriage. Three sons\nshared equally with their mother in the\ndivision of the estate. Herbert formerly\nwas on the stage In London.\n.jMMmammmmg\nPorch Paint L\nChoice of color* in good quality S\nDeck Paint\nBUTLER-RYNI\u00ae\n607-609 C St.\nMEtro. 0151\nPhone for Color Card\ni- F","height":"25413","width":"19701"}}
